quote: Toy Story 4 is a wonderful film, but as a sequel its a masterful display of how to move forward with franchise storytelling.
critic.name: Bianca Garner
publication.name: In Their Own League

quote: Toy Story 4's willingness to go to strange and dark places is part of its charm.
critic.name: Brian Eggert
publication.name: Deep Focus Review

quote: I found myself sobbing at the films conclusion because while Toy Story 3 felt like the conclusion to everyones story, Toy Story 4 showed us it was only Andys story that was complete. The toys story concluded with this film.
critic.name: David Gonzalez
publication.name: Reel Talk Inc.

quote: The second Toy Story was a sensation that led to Toy Story 3 and now 4. And what sensation exists in Toy Story 4!
critic.name: Steve Crum
publication.name: Crum on Showbiz

quote: These characters actually experience and that tiny shift really refreshes the franchise.
critic.name: Lonita Cook
publication.name: KCTV5 News at 9

quote: Kudos to Pixar for making yet another film that satisfies on so many levels.
critic.name: Hosea Rupprecht
publication.name: Pauline Center for Media Studies

quote: A sublime ending to a perfect franchise.
critic.name: Nick Reilly
publication.name: NME

quote: Pixar's franchise heads into new territory with this funny, poignant, charming road trip about passing on the baton.
critic.name: Katherine McLaughlin
publication.name: VODzilla.co

quote: It may not have truly needed to be made, but Toy Story 4 is just as good as any of the other films in the series and proves once again that Pixar is the undisputed master in the animation field.
critic.name: Alex Bentley
publication.name: CultureMap

quote: While I have to acknowledge that it isn't a particularly necessary movie, I also must say I'm so very glad they made it.
critic.name: Fletcher Powell
publication.name: KMUW - Wichita Public Radio

quote: What Pixar does so well is they take something familiar or, in this case, done thrice before, and make it fresh ... Toy Story 4 is a beautiful bookend to a story that holds a special place in the hearts of many.
critic.name: Candice McMillan
publication.name: Seattle Refined

quote: Although it's unusual for Pixar to continue a series for this long, if each new episode is going to remain this spectacular, keep them coming.
critic.name: Mike Massie
publication.name: Gone With The Twins

quote: Though the film covers much of the same ground from the three previous entries, there's still enough emotional gas in the tank to make this worth seeing.
critic.name: Charles Koplinski
publication.name: Reel Talk with Chuck and Pam

quote: Toy Story 4 is more like an epilogue than a new chapter. A funny, moving, surreal epilogue filled with existential angst.
critic.name: Robert Slack
publication.name: SooToday.com

quote: I'm not crying. You're crying.
critic.name: Richard Propes
publication.name: TheIndependentCritic.com

quote: Let's hope new renditions of Disney properties continue such correctives, and that genre revisionism will again be in service.
critic.name: Matthew Sorrento
publication.name: Film International

quote: Toy Story 4 proves there's still life in these toys in an emotionally heartfelt tale.
critic.name: Kelechi Ehenulo
publication.name: Confessions From A Geek Mind

quote: One of the most admirable things about Toy Story 4 is its refusal to bow to the easy call of nostalgia.
critic.name: Tom Beasley
publication.name: VultureHound

quote: At least the end result is a fun jaunt. Anything past this would just tug its threads to a fray.
critic.name: Matt Cipolla
publication.name: Film Monthly

quote: Josh Cooley's feature debut is yet another showcase of heartfelt entertainment, alive with energy and delivering yet another tear-jerking roundhouse of a finale.
critic.name: James Hanton
publication.name: Outtake Mag

quote: I notice the absence of magic, humor and sense of wonder that characterizes the three past films. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Yasser Medina
publication.name: Cinemaficionados

quote: If the "Toy Story" trilogy took us to infinity, the fourth installment just took us beyond. Here's hoping Woody hangs his hat here and goes out on top.
critic.name: Jason Fraley
publication.name: WTOP (Washington, D.C.)

quote: It plays like a nice, warm, final hug before we all have to grow up and move on.
critic.name: Allen Almachar
publication.name: The MacGuffin

quote: Woody and co will make you heartily smile in the heartfelt and wholesome fourth outing.
critic.name: Zehra Phelan
publication.name: Flavourmag

quote: Competently done, but is that all you expect from Toy Story?
critic.name: Doug Walker
publication.name: Channel Awesome

quote: It wastes none of its nearly two-hour screen time, packing the story with a lot of humanity and heart that guarantees once again that there are no dry eyes left once the credits roll.
critic.name: Nikki Francisco
publication.name: Nolisoli.ph

quote: A surprisingly fun and effective close to this venerable franchise.
critic.name: Damond Fudge
publication.name: KCCI (Des Moines, IA)

quote: Pixar is still operating at God-level here.
critic.name: Alex Hudson
publication.name: Exclaim!

quote: Not as good as the prior two entries, this film is a fitting, if less impressive, conclusion.
critic.name: Wesley Lovell
publication.name: Cinema Sight

quote: I appreciate the high-level creativity in the storytelling...although there's nothing new to see...
critic.name: Shawn Edwards
publication.name: Fox 4 Kansas City

quote: It appears they have found another perfect ending for the franchise, and it's time to listen to that inner-voice and close the toy box once and for all.
critic.name: Steven Sheehan
publication.name: The Digital Fix

quote: While not as good as the first two Toy Story pictures and probably not as good as the third, the heartfelt storyline and fun action scenes give audiences what they're looking for in a Pixar movie...
critic.name: Nick Boyd
publication.name: Battle Royale With Cheese

quote: Rare is a character who has both a one-note comedy beat (executed beautifully) and an extreme amount of emotional depth. What makes Forky so compelling is not his existential crisis, but his deep empathy for others...
critic.name: Ryan Silberstein
publication.name: Cinema76

quote: The latest adventure from a franchise that encourages us to find and express our purpose in life.
critic.name: Frederic and Mary Ann Brussat
publication.name: Spirituality & Practice

quote: Toy Story 4 is a wonderful film and a beautiful (maybe?) send-off for these characters. Take some time out this summer and see what will most likely be the best franchise movie of the year and possibly the early favorite for best-animated feature.
critic.name: Julian Lytle
publication.name: idobi.com

quote: The idea of a fourth Toy Story film was nothing short of troubling. Thankfully, graciously, and astoundingly, Toy Story 4 is fantastic.
critic.name: Damian Levy
publication.name: Jamaica Gleaner

quote: Nobody except the suits at Disney clamored for a fourth Toy Story movie, and yet Pixar somehow made an unnecessary sequel that feels indispensable.
critic.name: Daniel Barnes
publication.name: Sacramento News & Review

quote: Toy Story 4 is the first film in the series to introduce the concept that a toy can love another toy, and their developing relationship will pull at your heart.
critic.name: Kirk Baird
publication.name: Toledo Blade

quote: There are many wonderful surprises throughout. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Carlos Boyero
publication.name: El Pais (Spain)

quote: The film surpasses its predecessors as a work of supreme visual splendour: rendering the minutiae of a rainstorm, or (in a slightly more foreboding manner) the membranous layers of dust in an antique store with hyperreal precision.
critic.name: James Baxter
publication.name: PopMatters

quote: Not only is Toy Story 4 is the sequel I never knew I needed, it's quite possibly, the best Toy Story to ever be told.
critic.name: Mike Reyes
publication.name: CinemaBlend

quote: I admit that in the past I've felt skeptical of the need for a new Toy Story movie. But then one opens and it wins me over, finding new ways to wring emotion and heart from a story that appeared to have run its course.
critic.name: Adam Lubitow
publication.name: Rochester City Newspaper

quote: Director Josh Cooley offers plenty of excitement but he also introduces a raft of new characters -- from an antique store, a carnival and a bedroom that, frankly, has too many toys to begin with.
critic.name: Bruce R. Miller
publication.name: Sioux City Journal

quote: Toy Story 4 is the most fun film of 2019 so far, and the fact that it's also able to imbue this story with a catharsis, stakes and emotional moments is just icing on the cake.
critic.name: Ross Bonaime
publication.name: Brightest Young Things

quote: Not absolute top-flight Pixar. No embarrassment either.
critic.name: Donald Clarke
publication.name: Irish Times

quote: Toy Story 4 is more of a coda than a capstone. But given its strengths, maybe that's OK.
critic.name: Court Mann
publication.name: Deseret News (Salt Lake City)

quote: Pixar by the numbers, this third and largely unnecessary sequel to Toy Story delivers everything you'd expect from the animation studio, minus the warmth, wit, and dread.
critic.name: Ben Sachs
publication.name: Chicago Reader

quote: Toy Story 4 is so fast and light on its feet that it's easy to ignore that it's a pretty minor adventure.
critic.name: A.A. Dowd
publication.name: AV Club

quote: What might be the finale of this seminal series misses a chance to break new ground, but it ultimately lands on the truth about its central character.
critic.name: Neil Morris
publication.name: INDY Week

quote: Pixar pulls out all the stops for Toy Story 4. oy Story 4 provides the closure you didn't think you needed for this franchise.
critic.name: Paul McGuire Grimes
publication.name: KSTP-TV (St. Paul, MN)

quote: The existence of Forky (Tony Hale) foregrounds all sorts of existential questions that hover around the Toy Story premise. He asks the first one himself: "Why am I alive?" Best not to think about it too much, Forky.
critic.name: Chris McCoy
publication.name: Memphis Flyer

quote: It felt good to just come in and have a nice movie. This is just nice, and sweet, and endearing, and I think I kind of love it.
critic.name: Nathaniel Wayne
publication.name: Council of Geeks

quote: Although it may feel redundant, Toy Story 4 encapsulates the comedy, nostalgia and emotion that makes the series so great.
critic.name: Katie Smith-Wong
publication.name: Flick Feast

quote: As if being one of the greatest trilogies in film history wasn't enough for the Toy Story franchise, along comes a fourth feature that's just as fun, witty, and incredibly moving as the first three.
critic.name: Jeff York
publication.name: Creative Screenwriting

quote: Having only recently watched [Toy Story] 3, the closure in [Toy Story] 4 is more concrete and serves as a fitting conclusion for a series that's been about duty, friendship, and caring for others.
critic.name: Douglas Davidson
publication.name: Elements of Madness

quote: It is a bit of a reboot... If you can get past that, I think there are some wonderful, charming things here.
critic.name: Wade Major
publication.name: FilmWeek (KPCC - NPR Los Angeles)

quote: While I'm still not sure if Toy Story 4 is wholly necessary (3 ended things on such a beautiful note), the series still proves it has heart and visual creativity in unnatural abundance.
critic.name: Rhys Tarling
publication.name: Isolated Nation

quote: ...Toy Story 4 is beyond satisfying and tear-inducing (jeesh, Pixar give my tear ducts a break), with even more closure than the third installment.
critic.name: Jaime Davis
publication.name: MovieJawn

quote: While all of the "Toy Story" movies have dealt with themes of friendship and finding your place in the world, "Toy Story 4" drives home the fact the toys are emotional avatars for all of the parents in the audience.
critic.name: Mathew DeKinder
publication.name: Suburban Journals of St. Louis

quote: The fourth entry in Pixar's first and best franchise returns to some familiar places while finding a couple of new themes to explore. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mario Alegre
publication.name: Próxima Tanda

quote: Do not leave your seat until the very end of the credits - it will complete you.
critic.name: Kate Rodger
publication.name: Newshub (NZ)

quote: These big themes and rich ideas are perfect for the transition to wherever Disney Pixar intends to go after Toy Story 4.
critic.name: Jonita Davis
publication.name: The Black Cape

quote: Toy Story 4 justifies its existence by acting as an emotionally resonant epilogue to the series' perfect ending, and brings plenty of laughter and heartfelt moments throughout.
critic.name: Nicolás Delgadillo
publication.name: Cultured Vultures

quote: It was fun while it lasted but it's the first Toy Story movie to evaporate in the memory quickly after watching it. Which means it's the first non-essential entry.
critic.name: Nathaniel Rogers
publication.name: The Film Experience

quote: An excellent encore to one of the finest animated properties of the modern era.
critic.name: Brian Lloyd
publication.name: entertainment.ie

quote: Woody (Tom Hanks), Buzz Lightyear (Tim Allen) et al., we have a new toy (Forky) and another from the past (Bo Peep, voiced by Annie Potts), not to mention a magical toy store, and an ending that is bittersweet but just right for a finale to the series.
critic.name: Diane Pershing
publication.name: Malibu Times

quote: It would be frivolous to pretend that this fourth Toy Story has anything to add to the previous three or exists because of anything other than a commercial imperative.
critic.name: Stuart Klawans
publication.name: The Nation

quote: Fantastic writing and technical flourishes spruce up a Pixar sequel that doesn't have the emotional pull fans might expect.
critic.name: Mike Sorrentino
publication.name: CNET

quote: ...an enjoyable and periodically spellbinding endeavor that benefits substantially from its predictably eye-popping animation and raft of overtly entertaining vocal performances...
critic.name: David Nusair
publication.name: Reel Film Reviews

quote: ...bright, immensely moving and bracingly mature.
critic.name: Rubén Rosario
publication.name: MiamiArtZine

quote: The perfect finale to a beloved franchise about friendship and growing up.
critic.name: Linda Cook
publication.name: Quad City Times (Davenport, IA)

quote: Quibble about the necessity of this movie if you must but once the curtains are pulled and the opening credits begin, sit back and engross yourself in another magnificent adventure with Woody, Buzz, and the rest of the gang.
critic.name: Brian Gill
publication.name: Mad About Movies Podcast

quote: In a world where bonds, roles and stereotypes are being broken, the film's fervent preoccupation with characters realizing that there is more beyond what they originally perceived as their purpose of being feels timely and relevant.
critic.name: Oggs Cruz
publication.name: Rappler

quote: Toy Story 4 might not have a lot of new things going but it's still an amazingly fresh film.
critic.name: Mahmoud Mahdy
publication.name: FilmGamed

quote: This three-hanky picture further develops and strengthens the motivations of toy heroes-and miraculously, in a way that doesn't retread what came before it.
critic.name: Dominic Griffin
publication.name: Spectrum Culture

quote: Pixar has not only brought the saga of Woody, Buzz Lightyear and the rest of the toys back again, they've renewed the saga with style and heart, while keeping it from going stale.
critic.name: Robert Roten
publication.name: Laramie Movie Scope

quote: Toy Story 4, while entertaining fails to make a case as to why we needed another movie in this franchise. One of us loved and the other...not so much.
critic.name: Kaely Monahan
publication.name: Whiskey and Popcorn

quote: Pixar has raised the bar again in "Toy Story 4" in that the multitude of lessons to be learned are worth not only the price of admission but perhaps a fixture in the family movie library. Yes, it's that good.
critic.name: Sarah Knight Adamson
publication.name: Sarah's Backstage Pass

quote: The message it sends to a generation of young girls of benevolence, bravery, and independence, is what makes Toy Story 4 a truly great addition to an already stellar trilogy of films for everyone of every age and gender.
critic.name: Beth McDonough
publication.name: The Babbling Blonde

quote: While Toy Story 4 feels unnecessary in many ways, it finds things worth saying, story arcs to satisfy and will make you cry more frequently than it's predecessor managed.
critic.name: David Levesley
publication.name: GQ Magazine [UK]

quote: I call this movie unnecessary because the first three films told such a complete story, and this functions more as a "Where are they now?" follow-up. As such, however, it is wonderful.
critic.name: Asia Frey
publication.name: Lagniappe (Mobile, AL)

quote: Why the need for Part 4? There are new characters to merchandise!
critic.name: Scott Marks
publication.name: San Diego Reader

quote: There's a bit of overcompensating here, and there's too much attention given to the human characters...but it gets us emotionally involved, and the animation is spectacular.
critic.name: Lisa Nesselson
publication.name: France24

quote: This franchise has not skipped a single beat. Honestly, the franchise is as good, and in someways, better than it ever has been before. You don't need to be nervous. This is another heartwarming, very funny, Pixar classic.
critic.name: Sean Chandler
publication.name: Sean Chandler Talks About

quote: The toys are back in this wonderful animated experience that sweeps all expectations that a fourth entry may generate. [Full review in Spanish].
critic.name: Federico Furzan
publication.name: Cinelipsis

quote: This is the funniest Toy Story yet. ... [And it's] the first story in this world to focus on children as much as toys. In this, it raises important new questions.
critic.name: Jeffrey Overstreet
publication.name: Looking Closer

quote: A multilayered, hilarious and visually stunning complement to a story that has grown alongside its audience. You've got a friend in Pixar. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nestor Bentancor
publication.name: Nestor Cine Desde Hollywood

quote: It might not reach the heights of earlier installments, with little of the madcap inspiration that propelled the earlier films, but it still manages to arrive at a satisfying enough endpoint.
critic.name: Piers Marchant
publication.name: Arkansas Democrat-Gazette

quote: Put simply, it's a blast being in the company of these characters once again.
critic.name: Rob Carnevale
publication.name: Indie London

quote: Directed with energetic sincerity.
critic.name: Dann Gire
publication.name: Chicago Daily Herald

quote: [It's been] nearly a quarter-century... since the original Toy Story and this fourth installment is just as good.
critic.name: Lapacazo Sandoval
publication.name: New York Amsterdam News

quote: The tale is cathartic and moving, especially during an impressively mature climax that reminds us we didn't just grow up with the Toy Story series.
critic.name: Bennett Campbell Ferguson
publication.name: Willamette Week

quote: Toy Story 4 ended up being a pleasant surprise, with a story that explores searching for meaning in life and the self-discovery that happens along the way.
critic.name: Sarah Musnicky
publication.name: VitalThrills.com

quote: Despite some cute moments and an appealing cast of new and familiar characters, it never quite shakes the feeling of being wholly unnecessary.
critic.name: Matthew Lucas
publication.name: From the Front Row

quote: Disney manages to breathe new life into the Toy Story franchise and found a way to once again give a cohesive tale that again finishes Woody's saga as a childhood toy.
critic.name: Allison Rose
publication.name: FlickDirect

quote: Woody the cowboy, and to a lesser extent, Buzz the space ranger, return for a new entry in Pixar's flagship franchise that doesn't fail the high standards set by its predecessors.
critic.name: Dominic Corry
publication.name: New Zealand Herald

quote: This franchise has always been about the passage of time, and there's something poignant, powerful and fitting about seeing it playing out within a real-time context, almost 24 years after it began.
critic.name: Alison Gillmor
publication.name: Winnipeg Free Press

quote: It may not be a sequel we needed, but it's so downright charming that you'll be glad we were blessed with this chapter anyway.
critic.name: Sameen Amer
publication.name: The Express Tribune (Pakistan)

quote: Fun but oddly forgettable, it's a sequel you didn't ask for with an ending you'll still enjoy... now with more endings than a Stephen King novel.
critic.name: Kevin A. Ranson
publication.name: MovieCrypt.com

quote: Toy Story 4 is entertaining and eager to please, but what it's lacking is the gravitas of the previous three pictures. Is it time to put a fork(y) in the franchise?
critic.name: Matt Brunson
publication.name: Film Frenzy

quote: Is it the last one? Oh, come on...keep making these movies forever.
critic.name: Bob Grimm
publication.name: Reno News and Review

quote: Adding a dash of creepiness to the usual formula, Toy Story 4 exceeds expectations by - ahem - toying with them.
critic.name: Steve Biodrowski
publication.name: Cinefantastique

quote: This fourth Toy Story is the directorial debut of American animator, screenwriter and voice actor Josh Cooley. He does his best with what he has, but the script lacks spark.
critic.name: Stephen Romei
publication.name: The Australian

quote: Toy Story has been winning and warming hearts since 1995. Debutant director Josh Cooley takes charge of this fourth instalment, which boasts exemplary digital artistry.
critic.name: Udita Jhunjhunwala
publication.name: Livemint

quote: Compared to the other family offerings this summer, it is easily at the top of the pack. But when you compare it to the three films before it, this Toy Story isn't quite as wonderful as you might expect or hope it would be.
critic.name: Micheal Compton
publication.name: Bowling Green Daily News

quote: It's truly the best-looking movie Pixar has made to date.
critic.name: Spencer Perry
publication.name: ComingSoon.net

quote: It's a strikingly close imitation of what we're used to but features strong flavors of its own.
critic.name: George Elkind
publication.name: Metro Times (Detroit, MI)

quote: It's gag-a-minute filmmaking with zany, Looney Tunes energy, that covers a lot of plot at a brisk pace.
critic.name: Esther Zuckerman
publication.name: Thrillist

quote: Though the film seems like an unnecessary addition to the franchise (Toy Story 3 was also a hard act to follow) there is no doubting its ability to entertain.
critic.name: Paul Farren
publication.name: Film Ireland Magazine

quote: Pixar does pointlessness exceptionally well.
critic.name: Alistair Harkness
publication.name: Scotsman

quote: One of the most impressive technical achievements in the history of computer animation.
critic.name: Tim Brayton
publication.name: Alternate Ending

quote: In making Bo Peep such an engaging character, director Josh Cooley pulls one's attention away from the disjointed nature of the story.
critic.name: Courtney Small
publication.name: Cinema Axis

quote: Toy Story 4 is an intelligent film about transcending nostalgia and moving on. The perfect ending for a saga that has accompanied the dreams of a entire generation. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nicolás Ruiz
publication.name: Código espagueti

quote: Everything old is new again in this refreshing threequel. Plus you get just enough new characters to add to the fun. Woody and Bo - who knew!
critic.name: Jackie K. Cooper
publication.name: jackiekcooper.com

quote: It's amazing to see how a sequel that was initially perceived as unnecessary, ultimately became one of the best entries in the series. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Sebastian Zavala Kahn
publication.name: Cinencuentro

quote: Toy Story 4 may very well be the strongest film in the franchise with a heartfelt story that is full of laughter, warmth, and love, showing that four films later there is still plenty of life left in these toys.
critic.name: Matt Rodriguez
publication.name: Shakefire

quote: This may just be the best of the bunch, so get your tissues ready to join the gang one last time.
critic.name: Matt Hudson
publication.name: What I Watched Tonight

quote: The new movie matches elements of David Lynch aesthetics, R.L. Stine-inflected villainy, and Pixar's trademark heartstring-pulling. It pays off to incredible results.
critic.name: Abby Olcese
publication.name: Rave Reviews

quote: If the first three installments felt breezy and effortless, Cooley's movie feels forced and unimportant.
critic.name: Jordan Ruimy
publication.name: World of Reel

quote: Pixar delivers yet again by bringing different substance that reaches different age groups in their own way. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Hugo Hernández Valdivia
publication.name: Cinexcepción

quote: Toy Story 4 is full of great moments, comedy, empathy for toys and especially emotional and nostalgic moments that those who grew up with the franchise will value and those newer to it will enjoy it equally. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Israel Acosta Aroche
publication.name: Konexión

quote: Bright and shiny, with much of the third act set in and around a carnival, Toy Story 4 boasts impressive animation.
critic.name: Margot Harrison
publication.name: Seven Days

quote: Patriotic joking aside, there's a whole lot happening in Toy Story 4, the most amazing thing being how first-time feature director Josh Cooley manages to keep the overstuffed 100 minutes moving so fast and feeling so nimble.
critic.name: Chris Knight
publication.name: National Post

quote: It may derive from cynical commercial roots, but it's an undeniable pleasure to spend time with Woody and co. once more.
critic.name: David Brake
publication.name: One Room With A View

quote: Honestly, it's just about the best possible follow-up to a movie that seemingly needed no follow-up...I didn't want Toy Story 4 - but I sure am glad I got it.
critic.name: Allen Adams
publication.name: The Maine Edge

quote: Toy Story 4 delivers laughs, heart, and arguably the best performance by a spork of the past decade.
critic.name: Kent Garrison
publication.name: Mad About Movies Podcast

quote: There is SO MUCH TO LOVE. Even though the core gang is pushed to the side to give Bo, Woody & Forky the main spotlight, I was absolutely thrilled with the directions the characters were taken in, and also with the new characters that were introduced.
critic.name: Amie Simon
publication.name: Three Imaginary Girls

quote: ...see Toy Story 4 because it's one of the only franchise films this summer that doesn't stink up the joint; the other reason to see it is that's it's one of the best movies of the year.
critic.name: Steven Prokopy
publication.name: Third Coast Review

quote: Toy Story 4 is tender, but terrifying, warm, but risky and liberating, but wild. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Luis Martínez
publication.name: El Mundo (Spain)

quote: (John) Lasseter doesn't deserve such niceties, but this solid, entertaining film shows that, even without his input, Pixar will be just fine.
critic.name: Robert Ham
publication.name: The Stranger (Seattle, WA)

quote: Another new masterpiece. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: José Martín
publication.name: El antepenúltimo mohicano

quote: Toy Story has tiny bubbles of joy that do not dilute. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Natalia Trzenko
publication.name: La Nación (Argentina)

quote: Featuring a decent handful of great laugh-out-loud moments, Toy Story 4 is certainly terrific family entertainment, though it doesn't quite hit the emotional peaks delivered by Toy Story 3.
critic.name: Jim Schembri
publication.name: 3AW

quote: Woody and the gang are back in a sublime sequel that gets stolen by a spork named forky. Pixar just keeps topping itself.
critic.name: Pete Hammond
publication.name: Deadline Hollywood Daily

quote: Toy Story 4 is maybe the perfect conclusion to this series.
critic.name: Rachel Leishman
publication.name: The Mary Sue

quote: Toy Story 4 stands on the shoulders of its predecessors to deliver a wholly satisfying ending to this franchise-at least for now.
critic.name: Bryan Rolli
publication.name: The Daily Dot

quote: Toy Story 4 is a delight... and that alone is more than we could have reasonably expected of it and more than enough reason for it to exist at all.
critic.name: Paul Mount
publication.name: Starburst

quote: Toy Story 4 is a must-see for its beauty, drollery, and charm. But when it comes to the story, the boomerang maneuver is all it's got.
critic.name: Michael Sragow
publication.name: Film Comment Magazine

quote: Toy Story 4 is still great, and it works by respecting its predecessor's conclusive nature while offering a few additional thoughts rather than attempting to start over with a clean slate.
critic.name: Brendan Morrow
publication.name: The Week

quote: This might be just the most emotional experience you'll have in a cinema all year.
critic.name: James Croot
publication.name: Stuff.co.nz

quote: Everyone gets time to tell their story, whether it's Duke Caboom or Buzz Lightyear. Everyone has their moment in the spotlight.
critic.name: Ani Bundel
publication.name: NBC News THINK

quote: Toy Story 4 is fun and (does this even need saying of a Pixar film?) exceptionally well-made. If it doesn't live up to the towering effect of its predecessors, neither do most other movies.
critic.name: Abbie Bernstein
publication.name: Assignment X

quote: It feels like a nice, warm final hug before we all have to grow up and move on. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Ruben Peralta Rigaud
publication.name: Cocalecas

quote: Although the plot focuses on Pixar's exciting, expertly done rescues and escapes, "Toy Story 4" makes its masterstroke after those have played out.
critic.name: Jeffrey M. Anderson
publication.name: San Francisco Examiner

quote: Yet another funny, heartwarming, and uncommonly wise chapter in Pixar's enduring film series.
critic.name: Max Weiss
publication.name: Baltimore Magazine

quote: A film that must be seen. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: William Venegas
publication.name: La Nación (Costa Rica)

quote: This is what a family movie should be all about, wonderful visuals, meaningful ideas and gut-busting humor.
critic.name: Alci Rengifo
publication.name: Entertainment Voice

quote: A beacon of hope that reminds us that there is always more light at the end of the tunnel. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Emmanuel Báez
publication.name: Cinéfiloz

quote: Toy Story 4 is a surprise sequel I didn't think I needed, but adored it. Woody's character arc is something truly special.
critic.name: Lauren Veneziani
publication.name: WBAL-TV (Baltimore)

quote: After producing three brilliant Toy Story movies, I had my doubts that Pixar could pull off a fourth. I could not have been more off-base with that assessment.
critic.name: Mike McGranaghan
publication.name: Film Racket

quote: Despite its dubious "necessity", Toy Story 4 adds an emotionally ambitious, tear-jerking post-script to Pixar's flagship franchise.
critic.name: Shaun Munro
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: The new film is a revelation because it does not pretend to imitate its predecessor, but manages to recover the spirit of the first film of 1995 to offer a new round of light comedy and vivid adventures. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Luis Fernando Galván
publication.name: En Filme

quote: Pixar retrieves its toys with the usual mastery, but without the magic that has made the studio great. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Víctor López G.
publication.name: Espinof

quote: Toy Story 4 delivers us a cinema that has disappeared from our lives in the same way that our childhood toys did from our imaginations. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fausto Fernandez
publication.name: Fotogramas

quote: Tradition has turned out to be Pixar's heart-light.
critic.name: Tom Shone
publication.name: Sunday Times (UK)

quote: But for all that I enjoyed it, for all that it will play to happily packed cinemas over the summer... there is a bit of me that wishes they'd called it a day after Toy Story 3. But maybe that's just me.
critic.name: Matthew Bond
publication.name: The Mail on Sunday (UK)

quote: Although it is not the best movie in the series, it manages to honor the legacy of its predecessors and gives us a story worthy of these beloved characters. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Arturo Magaña
publication.name: Cine Premiere

quote: Kids will watch Toy Story 4 with wide eyes enjoying the whole ride and not fully understanding how good what they're seeing actually is.
critic.name: Matt Ward
publication.name: Cinematic Considerations

quote: It provides some laughs and a lot of heart but, in the end, it feels like a footnote to the toys' adventures.
critic.name: Matthew Passantino
publication.name: Big Picture Big Sound

quote: Stunning animation and a storyline filled with adventure, comedy, and a few frights (as with any good Disney film) make this a welcomed return to the Pixar franchise.
critic.name: Joe Friar
publication.name: The Victoria Advocate

quote: A majestic epilogue.
critic.name: Cameron Frew
publication.name: FrewFilm

quote: It provides a resolution for all the toys, which though predicated on the same idea as previous films, namely each toy finding their purpose, gives that theme expression in a way that feels more individuated to the characters and satisfying.
critic.name: Ed Whitfield
publication.name: The Ooh Tray

quote: Darn you Pixar, just take your Oscar already you incredible masters of storytelling and animation.
critic.name: Rendy Jones
publication.name: Rendy Reviews

quote: There's no wrong way to respond to a movie, and I'll agree that Toy Story 4 isn't perfect, it's merely excellent. Is it too much of a good thing? Perhaps, but the fact remains that it's still a good thing.
critic.name: Tim Brennan
publication.name: About Boulder

quote: A beautiful coda to the Toy Story Trilogy, Toy Story 4 provides a perfect epilogue for these beloved characters with strong emotional beats, powerful themes and hilarious moments.
critic.name: Sheraz Farooqi
publication.name: CinemaDebate

quote: Cooley's film quickens and deepens...
critic.name: Anthony Lane
publication.name: New Yorker

quote: Toy Story 4 is so good it's criminal. The legislation it flouts is the law of diminishing returns which governs movies with numbers after their names.
critic.name: Matthew Norman
publication.name: London Evening Standard

quote: Both hilarious and disturbing, the near-perfect Toy Story 4 doesn't shy away from the big questions, delving into sentience and self-determination around the slapstick.
critic.name: Sarah Cartland
publication.name: Caution Spoilers

quote: Another funny and touching entry into the most iconic Pixar saga. A colorful and imaginative adventure where our beloved characters question their purpose in life. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Rene Sanchez
publication.name: Cine Sin Fronteras

quote: Like its predecessors, Toy Story 4's characters frequently question their own nature, their role in the universe, what they wish for their lives and how those wishes fare against reality. [Full review in Portuguese.]
critic.name: Pablo Villaça
publication.name: Cinema em Cena

quote: The latest installment, "Toy Story 4," is perhaps the bleakest (and most beautiful) of them all.
critic.name: Matthew Rozsa
publication.name: Salon.com

quote: The feature-film CG-animated series that changed the industry is gorgeously & hilariously completed...be entertained by...the best friends any film goer could ask for!
critic.name: Colby Bryant
publication.name: Colbybryant.com

quote: While [this] many cooks will always give a discerning viewer pause as to a finished product's quality, Toy Story 4 was somehow baked to perfection.
critic.name: Jared Mobarak
publication.name: The Film Stage

quote: My least favorite of the four, but least favorite compared to three grade-A movies is still pretty good.
critic.name: Eric D. Snider
publication.name: Crooked Marquee

quote: If you can get past the bummer that is the lack of an opening short, you'll be glad you did.
critic.name: Luke Hicks
publication.name: Film School Rejects

quote: Not groundbreaking or as heartfelt as other entries, Toy Story 4 is still an enjoyable ride with your favorite toys.
critic.name: EJ Moreno
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: Pixar keeps coming up with lovable characters inhabiting relatable stories, culminating in a bittersweet conclusion. It's wholesome, enjoyable entertainment for the entire family.
critic.name: Susan Granger
publication.name: SSG Syndicate

quote: TOY STORY 4 handles its heavy doses of philosophical queries with maturity, nuance, and tenderness, never once eyeballing the children in the audience, never once demanding not enough or too much.
critic.name: Bill Arceneaux
publication.name: Big Easy Magazine

quote: In terms of sheer plot construction and emotional precision, it's definitely the weakest of the series. But there's a newfound ambition here that cleverly and satisfying rewrites the core of the franchise into something that's really life-affirming.
critic.name: Matthew Dougherty
publication.name: The Filtered Lens

quote: Nine years have passed since Woody, Buzz Lightyear and the gang last did their irrepressible bit, but the intrepid buddies have lost none of their bounce.
critic.name: Andiee Paviour
publication.name: Nobody's Reading This But Me

quote: For now, thanks to a highly-engaging ride that bursts with full-of-heart performances, asks essential questions, and treats us to exciting entrants and action sequences, Toy Story 4 more than justifies its presence.
critic.name: Akhil Arora
publication.name: Gadgets360

quote: This is a brilliant movie.
critic.name: S. Indra Sathiabalan
publication.name: The Sun Daily (Malaysia)

quote: Toy Story 4 proves, once again, that there's still life left in this charming and smart franchise.
critic.name: Wenlei Ma
publication.name: News.com.au

quote: Toy Story 4 is a straight-up sequel with all your favorites returning - if nostalgia is more your thing, you know what to do.
critic.name: Kaitlin Reilly
publication.name: Refinery29

quote: Toy Story 4 is a joyous addition to this beloved Pixar franchise. It has so much heart and lets the characters drive the story, their growth a natural progression in their journeys.
critic.name: Mae Abdulbaki
publication.name: The Young Folks

quote: One kid's trash is another little girl's treasure - or, in this case, toy ... bringing with him existential angst and affirmation.
critic.name: Annlee Ellingson
publication.name: L.A. Biz

quote: Ultimately, it's perhaps a deft, intelligent appendix to the previous priceless trio, but the story's cross-generation appeal remains strong, and the whole production has far more integrity than the cash-in job the cynics were expecting.
critic.name: Trevor Johnston
publication.name: Radio Times

quote: Bad news: Toy Story 4 is Pixar's biggest money grab to date. Good news: This is Pixar, so it never feels like one.
critic.name: Frank Wilkins
publication.name: Reel Reviews

quote: The result is a well made fourth film, which appeals to the characters that became endearing over the years. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Lucero Calderón
publication.name: Excelsior

quote: Even in its fourth instalment, Toy Story not only remains highly relevant, but also elevates the franchise to newer highs of cinematic excellence.
critic.name: Ronak Kotecha
publication.name: The Times of India

quote: Toy Story 4 is clever and witty, at times exhilarating, and does the little tap dance on your tear ducts that you've come to crave from Pixar films, and especially from this franchise.
critic.name: Kevin Fallon
publication.name: The Daily Beast

quote: The fourth Toy Story movie is yet another delight, with beautiful animation, a glittering voice cast, some gorgeous gags, innovative touches, and a typically Pixar serving of sincere feeling.
critic.name: David 'Mad Dog' Bradley
publication.name: Adelaide Review

quote: Though on the surface it may seem like another trip back to the well, it is acutely aware of its own age and doesn't try to retcon anything that hasn't already been perfectly resolved.
critic.name: Jennifer Heaton
publication.name: Alternative Lens

quote: Toy Story 4 is the most complex and the most adult film of the franchise so far.
critic.name: Devesh Sharma
publication.name: Filmfare

quote: Toy Story 4 functions as a reverent send-off for both Woody and Hanks, with a denouement every bit as stingingly sweet as Endgame's...
critic.name: Rob Harvilla
publication.name: The Ringer

quote: I think it's a standalone in itself. I think it's really good, and it has validity of its own, and it should be done now.
critic.name: Mark Kermode
publication.name: Kermode & Mayo's Film Review

quote: With its constantly smart humor (from eight credited screenwriters), a few more unexpected vocal cameos, and the franchise's ever-evident emotion, recycling never has felt so fresh.
critic.name: John Urbancich
publication.name: Your Movies (cleveland.com)

quote: If you need some happiness in your life this weekend, Toy Story 4 is the movie to watch...to infinity and beyond, etc.
critic.name: Sucharita Tyagi
publication.name: Film Companion

quote: They made a really well-rounded villain, I appreciate that.
critic.name: Achara Kirk
publication.name: GET Jaby

quote: The animation was just so good, that alone makes the film worthwhile before the emotional aspect...
critic.name: Jaby Koay
publication.name: GET Jaby

quote: I laughed so hard throughout this entire movie. Funniest of 2019 so far, easily.
critic.name: Martin Thomas
publication.name: Double Toasted

quote: The storytelling is very tight. Everything works together.
critic.name: Korey Coleman
publication.name: Double Toasted

quote: Toy Story 4 undergoes a meta treatment that works beautifully, resonates emotionally, and should finally wrap up Pixar's Toy Story franchise.
critic.name: Roxana Hadadi
publication.name: Pajiba

quote: I have no complaints. Cute, heart-warming with a beautiful message.
critic.name: Steph Cozza
publication.name: Aggressive Comix

quote: Watching the gang...hide the fact that they're living beings coexisting in our world is exhausting. You want them to exclaim, 'We're here! We're dear! Play with us!'
critic.name: Randy Shulman
publication.name: Metro Weekly (Washington, DC)

quote: It's a no-brainer...I cried, and I liked it a lot more than I thought I was going to...
critic.name: Andre Meadows
publication.name: Black Nerd Comedy

quote: At the heart of the movie is a lesson for Woody. In him, I see hints of myself as I prepare for my youngest daughter's current transition as a high school graduate heading off to college.
critic.name: tt stern-enzi
publication.name: Cincinnati CityBeat

quote: Toy Story 4 is a work of genuine humanism not all that dissimilar from Milton's Paradise Lost.
critic.name: Walter Chaw
publication.name: Film Freak Central

quote: Toy Story 4 balances real issues, fun and undisguised sentiment.
critic.name: Robert Denerstein
publication.name: Denerstein Unleashed

quote: Of all the Toy Story films, 4 asks us to learn to be comfortable with bringing new things to life, and saying farewell to the things we once loved.
critic.name: Dom Nero
publication.name: Esquire Magazine

quote: Toy Story is now a quartet of great movies, with a fantastic new installment to make audiences laugh, gasp and, yes, cry - again.
critic.name: Brandy McDonnell
publication.name: The Oklahoman

quote: Toy Story 4, despite minor hiccups, is still a welcoming breath of familiar air in the otherwise lacklustre season of blockbuster sequels.
critic.name: Melalin Mahavongtrakul
publication.name: Bangkok Post

quote: The new movie works hard to entertain, but it's also stuck in awkward limbo between reset and replay mode, gesturing toward new adventures while rehashing tired old themes.
critic.name: Luke Goodsell
publication.name: ABC News (Australia)

quote: As with Incredibles 2 and Finding Dory, it's slick and inventive enough to make time spent with old friends pass quickly and warmly, with plenty of laughs as well as a few tears.
critic.name: Steven D. Greydanus
publication.name: National Catholic Register

quote: It's stronger for all the roads it didn't take: no scatological humor, no hammering of politically correct messages, no garish pop tunes wedged in to keep the energy up.
critic.name: Lisa Johnson Mandell
publication.name: AtHomeInHollywood.com

quote: Although it lacks the humor of earlier Toy Story films, this sequel is chock full of heart and emotion. Great for younger audiences.
critic.name: Julia Swift
publication.name: My Champlain Valley

quote: Toy Story 4 is a good movie... [But] no matter how many laughs will be had or tears shed, it still isn't strong enough to justify its existence."
critic.name: Nick Johnston
publication.name: Vanyaland

quote: The gang's all there, immediately reminding viewers why Pixar stands out above other animated features, stirring the emotions of adults and kids alike.
critic.name: Pamela Powell
publication.name: Daily Journal (Kankakee, IL)

quote: While the film rarely approaches the existential gut punch of Toy Story 3's conclusion, the various answers each of our heroes arrive at are among the most moving of the quartet.
critic.name: Christopher Machell
publication.name: CineVue

quote: It doesn't put you through the emotional wringer the way its predecessor did, but it's consistently inventive, funny, witty, and heartfelt. In other words, it's a lot better than it has any right to be. It's more than good enough to justify its existence.
critic.name: Peter Rainer
publication.name: Christian Science Monitor

quote: "Toy Story 4" is the single best film of 2019 thus far and if there are films that top it throughout the year, what a year of cinema we have been blessed with.
critic.name: Clayton Davis
publication.name: AwardsCircuit.com

quote: Toy Story 4 is absolutely delightful for adults and children.
critic.name: Diane Carson
publication.name: KDHX (St. Louis)

quote: Solidifies Toy Story's place as the best franchise in cinematic history.
critic.name: Kiko Martinez
publication.name: San Antonio Current

quote: ...we find a new opportunity to connect with these characters all over again.
critic.name: Michael Ward
publication.name: Should I See It

quote: Yes, another Disney/Pixar sequel. But surprisingly dark and existential, equal part Keaton and Kafka.
critic.name: James Verniere
publication.name: Boston Herald

quote: Although undoubtedly pleasant, it seems to have a thesis that life is about moving on and not repeating behaviors out of fear. That's a fine sentiment but super weird to hear from the fourth movie in a franchise where every film has had the same plot.
critic.name: Ryan Syrek
publication.name: The Reader (Omaha, NE)

quote: Pixar continues to indoctrinate viewers into childish, compulsive consumerism.
critic.name: Armond White
publication.name: National Review

quote: With its trademark clever adventures and stunning animation, Toy Story 4 is a worthy addition to a franchise that has grown up along with its audience. (BKP: 5/5)
critic.name: Brigid Presecky
publication.name: FF2 Media

quote: Toy Story 4 isn't as much of a tearjerker as its predecessors, but the franchise retains a powerful grasp on the emotions of its audience.
critic.name: Ian Thomas Malone
publication.name: Ian Thomas Malone

quote: The third film seemed like the perfect concluding point, but "4," directed by Josh Cooley, goes in a slightly new direction while hitting all the right notes.
critic.name: Tom Meek
publication.name: Cambridge Day

quote: [Toy Story 4] is, for all intents and purposes, Toy Story's version of The Velveteen Rabbit.
critic.name: Emmet Asher-Perrin
publication.name: Tor.com

quote: I didn't expect Toy Story 4 to give me evil doll nightmares and philosophical dread over my own baffling existence. Still, how glad I am that it did.
critic.name: Jeva Lange
publication.name: The Week

quote: Part of me wants the series to go out now on a high note - but then, I thought that after "Toy Story 2" and "Toy Story 3." After nearly a quarter-century, the series' battery life shows no signs of running low.
critic.name: Rob Thomas
publication.name: Capital Times (Madison, WI)

quote: The magic of "Toy Story 4" and these movies is seen in that incredible balance of making great entertainment, while at the same time making simple but all-important comments on our human existence.
critic.name: Michael Smith
publication.name: Tulsa World

quote: Finding your purpose, embracing your destiny and accepting your mortality are mature themes for a children's film, but "Toy Story 4" handles them nimbly while still managing to be a colorful family adventure.
critic.name: Adam Graham
publication.name: Detroit News

quote: A complex and not necessarily entirely cohesive story doesn't stop the plot points from delivering solid impact.
critic.name: Phil Villarreal
publication.name: ABC Tucson

quote: While [Toy Story 4] doesn't feel like an addition anyone needed, it's certainly not one that deserves to be thrown in the trash.
critic.name: Rain Jokinen
publication.name: MullingMovies.com

quote: The film's themes of moving on and letting go become unexpectedly poignant, with real weight behind them. But then this is the world of Toy Story, so we should have expected it.
critic.name: Robert Horton
publication.name: HeraldNet (Everett, WA)

quote: The newest 'Story' overflows with humor, heart and insights into the human condition. Not bad for analog toys.
critic.name: Christian Toto
publication.name: HollywoodInToto.com

quote: Toy Story 4 is wholly superfluous, albeit often funny and nice to look at.
critic.name: Joel Mayward
publication.name: Cinemayward

quote: Though it doesn't quite go to infinity and beyond, "Toy Story 4" offers a soothing conclusion to this comradery of characters. Forky and Duke Kaboom are guaranteed to become your new favorite obsession.
critic.name: Nate Adams
publication.name: The Only Critic

quote: All of which is to say that Toy Story 4 is really about parenthood.
critic.name: Sonny Bunch
publication.name: Washington Free Beacon

quote: People that fell in love with the franchise as kids are now in their 30s and 40s. The series has grown up with them. That's what's mostly wrong here. Toys ought not grow up.
critic.name: Gary Wolcott
publication.name: KXL-FM (Portland, OR)

quote: A fun-filled, vibrant, wacky and heartfelt adventure that is a treat for everyone.
critic.name: Scott Davis
publication.name: HeyUGuys

quote: As much as this feels like an unnecessary sequel, Pixar has done the impossible. It's turned the perfect trilogy into the perfect quadrilogy.
critic.name: Matt Neal
publication.name: ABC Radio (Australia)

quote: It is at this point that we must ask ourselves, how much of a good thing is too much?
critic.name: Rohan Naahar
publication.name: Hindustan Times

quote: This left me in tears proving the power of Pixar is still intact with the Toy Story franchise. New characters like Forky make it funky fresh and ready for a whole new generation to fall in love all over again. Family Summer fun for kids and adults.
critic.name: Carla Renata
publication.name: The Curvy Film Critic

quote: Woody learns that everything eventually must end...everything apparently except the Toy Story movies.
critic.name: Tom Santilli
publication.name: Movie Show Plus

quote: Toy Story 4 is not your father's Toy Story - or, not your childhood's Toy Story.
critic.name: Jason McKiernan
publication.name: Film Racket

quote: Toy Story 4 still orbits the "friendship is good" universe established by the first Toy Story, but it reaches for much deeper meaning by asking what it means to live purposefully.
critic.name: Sarah Marrs
publication.name: Lainey Gossip

quote: Toy Story 4 captures the heart of the entire saga in its own way.
critic.name: Alan Ng
publication.name: Film Threat

quote: Toy Story 4 is potentially the most adult film Pixar has ever made. Its emotions are complex. Its story does not make simple choices.
critic.name: Grant Watson
publication.name: Fiction Machine

quote: So, after the brilliant and emotional conclusion to Toy Story 3, was there possibly anything left to be said? As it turns out, there was.
critic.name: Daniel M. Kimmel
publication.name: North Shore Movies

quote: While it may still feel like a stretch, it's a sweet continuation with fun new characters, lots of laughs and plenty of heart. So, if a fourth movie in the franchise had to be made, 'Toy Story 4' is about as good as it could be.
critic.name: Preston Barta
publication.name: Denton Record-Chronicle

quote: Toy Story 4 may be a nostalgic trip for those who grew up with the series, but it will also bring much joy to a new generation of viewers.
critic.name: Joanne Soh
publication.name: The New Paper (Singapore)

quote: The folks at Pixar care too much about the beloved Toy Story characters to completely mail it in. And although Toy Story 4 lacks the levels of wit and charm of its predecessors, it does have its winning moments.
critic.name: Clint O'Connor
publication.name: Akron Beacon Journal

quote: Toy Story 4 is finely crafted and gorgeously detailed -- everything we have come to expect from this particular Pixar franchise.
critic.name: Theresa Smith
publication.name: Weekend Special (South Africa)

quote: Toy Story 4 achieves the near impossible. It's an emotionally rewarding film that joyfully reintroduces old friends alongside a new roster of engaging characters.
critic.name: Mark Daniell
publication.name: Toronto Sun

quote: The new film isn't flawless, but it's hugely enjoyable and speaks, with bewitching buoyancy, to nothing less than the purpose of living and the mystery of life.
critic.name: Joe Morgenstern
publication.name: Wall Street Journal

quote: Toy Story 4 lacks the heart and originality of the original trilogy but it remains a fun distraction with Woody and the gang.
critic.name: Kristen Lopez
publication.name: Culturess

quote: Do we really need another one? If the films continue to offer the innocent hilarity the latest does-yes, please, keep them coming!
critic.name: Megan Basham
publication.name: WORLD

quote: Toy Story 4 is as mediocre a Toy Story movie as there is and probably can be, but it also marks another unbelievable triumph at Pixar in their never-ending quest to realize the imagination.
critic.name: Luke Parker
publication.name: We Got This Covered

quote: The word 'fine' is often taken as an insult, but there are instances where it is the appropriate way to describe something, and this is one of them. This movie is fine.
critic.name: David Medsker
publication.name: Bullz-Eye.com

quote: It might not be a necessary installment in the series, but it isn't an unnecessary one, either...
critic.name: Mark Dujsik
publication.name: Mark Reviews Movies

quote: The funniest entry of the series. One that once again entertains with gorgeous visuals, plenty of charm and lots of heart. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fico Cangiano
publication.name: CineXpress

quote: Funny, thoughtful, charming, emotionally engaging, filled with creative details, and makes you realize just how much you missed Woody, Buzz and the rest of the gang. (Full Content Review for Parents - Scary Scenes, etc. - also Available)
critic.name: Jim Judy
publication.name: Screen It!

quote: "You've Got a Friend in Me" is a veritable golden oldie. But Toy Story 4 is very much an antique still worth cherishing.
critic.name: Peter Howell
publication.name: Toronto Star

quote: Toy Story 4 is an action-packed animation about growing up and moving on.
critic.name: Vicky Roach
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (Australia)

quote: Watching animated characters who are written with such depth, performed with such commitment, and brought to life with such care is pure movie magic.
critic.name: Victor Stiff
publication.name: That Shelf

quote: Every bit as lovable as the first three films, its mixture of rambunctious fun and sentimental schmaltz is utterly irresistible...a combination of the familiar and the new that makes for an instant classic.
critic.name: Frank Swietek
publication.name: One Guy's Opinion

quote: A funny, freaky, often profound animated adventure that is certainly the best movie ever made about a spork.
critic.name: Gary Thompson
publication.name: Philadelphia Daily News

quote: The toybox gets even larger in "Toy Story 4," a busy but entertaining entry in the best animated franchise the movies have.
critic.name: Chris Hewitt
publication.name: Minneapolis Star Tribune

quote: One takes the voice work of Tom Hanks for granted in these films, but he is their heart and soul and is quite superb here as a stuffed cowboy who's running out of road.
critic.name: Paul Whitington
publication.name: Irish Independent

quote: Perhaps, like Woody, it's time to consign the "Toy Story" franchise to a cinematic closet before all the good will it has accrued over the years turns to dust.
critic.name: Bob Bloom
publication.name: Journal and Courier (Lafayette, IN)

quote: Toy Story 4 may be the most adult film in the set so far, one that explores the possibility of a second independent life for empty-nester parents.
critic.name: Pamela Hutchinson
publication.name: Sight & Sound

quote: The opening sequence featuring a torrential downpour, is a masterpiece of digital artistry.
critic.name: Saskia Baron
publication.name: The Arts Desk

quote: I was dubious about the first sequel to Pixar's wonderfulToy Story,which turned out to be terrific. This is a highly enjoyable film with laugh-out-loud gags, ingenious plotting, and endearing new characters.
critic.name: Leonard Maltin
publication.name: leonardmaltin.com

quote: [Nothing] has changed in terms of the emotions, the humor, the solidarity between friendly toys and the amazing creativity in the animation. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Pablo O. Scholz
publication.name: Clarín

quote: "Toy Story 4" isn't in the running for franchise best, it may even be the "worst" of the series, but it's still hard to imagine that anyone would be more disappointed than delighted here.
critic.name: Brad Keefe
publication.name: Columbus Alive

quote: Though it springs fewer surprises, Toy Story 4 is still reliably fab.
critic.name: Jasper Rees
publication.name: The Spectator

quote: Happily, the long wait has paid off.
critic.name: John Lui
publication.name: The Straits Times (Singapore)

quote: Toy Story 4 is a wonderful film and proof positive that a sequel -- a third sequel, no less -- can be just as strong and smart and surprising as the work that it sprang from, provided that it has been made with the same degree of care and ambition.
critic.name: Peter Sobczynski
publication.name: eFilmCritic.com

quote: A movie that speaks simultaneously to us, to itself, to all of its predecessors, and to the culture that shaped it, and that it has helped shape.
critic.name: Matt Zoller Seitz
publication.name: RogerEbert.com

quote: To infinity, and beyond.
critic.name: Michael J. Casey
publication.name: Boulder Weekly

quote: TS4 is still flying high on visual pow, pinwheeling fun and soulful feeling. And oh that Forky! As voiced by the incomparable Tony Hale, this plastic spork is an animated character for the ages.
critic.name: Peter Travers
publication.name: Rolling Stone

quote: Toying with us again, Disney/Pixar applies another fresh coat of paint.
critic.name: Roger Tennis
publication.name: Cinemaclips.com

quote: It's too bad the surrounding story is less than riveting ...but at least Bo Peep gives it something of a charge to carry us through to the end.
critic.name: Christopher Llewellyn Reed
publication.name: Film Festival Today

quote: My emotional investment in the story was pretty much zilch, but I marveled over the depth of field, the nuance of expression, the way shadows and light played on these plasticine faces.
critic.name: Kimberley Jones
publication.name: Austin Chronicle

quote: The animation is striking, the jokes amusing and the story sweet, though this being Pixar, the tale is also melancholic enough that the whole thing feels deeper than it is.
critic.name: Manohla Dargis
publication.name: New York Times

quote: Pixar's writers know how to stir our emotions (even when we try hard not to cry, they get us every time).
critic.name: Jo Berry
publication.name: Movies4Kids

quote: Mildly amusing and profoundly unnecessary, it's got everything you're looking for except for anything new.
critic.name: Sean Burns
publication.name: The ARTery

quote: "Toy Story 4" avoids sequel pitfalls.
critic.name: Charles Koplinski
publication.name: Illinois Times

quote: Although parting is such sweet sorrow, I hope this is goodbye. It's time to go and the ending offers a graceful, hopeful exit.
critic.name: James Berardinelli
publication.name: ReelViews

quote: This fourth entry in a series...long recognized as dealing with love and mortality, is a spiritual allegory that finds Woody submitting to an 'organ transplant' to give new life to another before ascending to his own version of heaven.
critic.name: Laura Clifford
publication.name: Reeling Reviews

quote: The talents all gel, combining the history and character so beautifully articulated over a quarter century with some really fresh and very funny ideas.
critic.name: Hope Madden
publication.name: Columbus Underground

quote: Even if no one needs a Toy Story 4, it's here, and the good news is that it's funny and imaginative and, in places, intriguingly strange.
critic.name: Stephanie Zacharek
publication.name: TIME Magazine

quote: It's enough to make you feel like a kid again.
critic.name: Maren Longbella
publication.name: St. Paul Pioneer Press

quote: In this fourth and final chapter of these beloved toys, we are treated to their wisdom, hilarity and triumphant spirit all over again.
critic.name: Jeanne Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: So many funny lines and dialogue exchanges aimed at adults abound that young children will be perplexed as to why their parents are laughing.
critic.name: David Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: Toy Story 4 is the type of soul-warming cinema experience we didn't know we needed, but are thankful all the same that it exists.
critic.name: Peter Gray
publication.name: The AU Review

quote: Walking out of the theatre afterwards I knew for certain I just watched one of the best motion pictures I'd see in all of 2019.
critic.name: Sara Michelle Fetters
publication.name: MovieFreak.com

quote: The Toy Story movies exist to delight children and rip out the hearts of adults, offering bittersweet endings to some characters while letting others get increasingly bizarre.
critic.name: Norman Wilner
publication.name: NOW Toronto

quote: Despite some good work by Hanks, it lacks the heart of the first three films.
critic.name: Tyler Smith
publication.name: Battleship Pretension

quote: The fourth installment of this winning series has all the hallmarks of its predecessors: superb storytelling plus great characters and multi-generational appeal. Be sure to bring Kleenex.
critic.name: Karen Gordon
publication.name: Original Cin

quote: For millennial audiences who've grown up with Woody and the gang over years of toy stories, the movie may even seem a minor miracle - proof that faith can be kept in a faithless world.
critic.name: Ty Burr
publication.name: Boston Globe

quote: Saddle up for one more ride with the old gang. More a nostalgia tour than a full entry to Pixar's cornerstone franchise, Toy Story 4 is still fun and family-friendly curtain call.
critic.name: Christopher Lloyd
publication.name: The Film Yap

quote: "Toy Story 4" isn't better than the original trilogy, but it is undeniably funny, sweet, and it will probably make you reach for a tissue or two by the film's very end.
critic.name: Kirsten Acuna
publication.name: Insider

quote: Toy Story 4 genially and entertainingly proves that its titular playthings still have some mileage left in them.
critic.name: Andrew Parker
publication.name: The Gate

quote: Some storytelling angel presides over this series.
critic.name: Kristian M. Lin
publication.name: Fort Worth Weekly

quote: We take this magic for granted these days, just as we take for granted how hard to it must be to pull off a film as well as Toy Story 4 does.
critic.name: Jason Gorber
publication.name: HighDef Digest

quote: Toy Story 4 proves that the franchise is still the best. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Benjamín Harguindey
publication.name: EscribiendoCine

quote: Long after the contrived and misfired bits have faded, the brilliantly visualized action sequences and the pinpricks of emotion stay with you.
critic.name: Justin Chang
publication.name: NPR

quote: Forky's plight is utterly relatable in these trying times, as he plaintively queries the universe, "trash?" before hurtling his frame into the void of space.
critic.name: Katie Walsh
publication.name: Tribune News Service

quote: The visuals are so impressive that I reached the point where I wasn't sure whether Cooley and his army of Pixar technicians inserted "real" elements like rain and grass into a digitally animated landscape, like a backward Who Framed Roger Rabbit.
critic.name: Barry Hertz
publication.name: Globe and Mail

quote: Maybe it wasn't the most necessary sequel on the planet, but once you see the movie Toy Story 4 it will be impossible to see the saga without this film. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Abigail Camarillo
publication.name: Chilango.com

quote: "Toy Story 4" moves along briskly for 100 minutes, with the level of animation excellence you'd expect from Pixar.
critic.name: Maria Sciullo
publication.name: Pittsburgh Post-Gazette

quote: Toy Story 4 solidifies that Pixar has crafted one of the best film franchises of all time, if not the best.
critic.name: Scott Menzel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: Toy Story 4 has the wings and claws of a great melodrama. Nobody today can drill into childhood trauma like Pixar.
critic.name: Richard von Busack
publication.name: MetroActive

quote: Pixar have created another near-perfect family film while ever so slightly deviating from their expected formula. If this is the start to a second trilogy, then based on what I've seen here, I'll follow it to infinity and beyond.
critic.name: Alistair Ryder
publication.name: Film Inquiry

quote: While so many other franchises regurgitate the same old same old in what feels like a corporate cash grab, Toy Story has maintained its sweet, funny and very touching freshness.
critic.name: Joanna Langfield
publication.name: The Movie Minute

quote: If the series really is bowing out, it's doing so very gracefully.
critic.name: Sandra Hall
publication.name: Sydney Morning Herald

quote: At a moment when studios and pundits have begun again to question the efficacy of sequels, Pixar's graceful follow-up justifies the practice, when executed with smarts and heart.
critic.name: Peter Canavese
publication.name: Groucho Reviews

quote: Enjoyable and energetic but hardly essential, this is a piece you could pluck from the Toy Story canon and never notice its absence. That's a far cry from the ways in which this franchise has always challenged itself to reach for the sky.
critic.name: Nick Rogers
publication.name: Midwest Film Journal

quote: Sure, you cannot improve upon perfection. But Toy Story 4 shows us you can hold a mirror up to it, reflect it, honour it, and leave that perfection intact.
critic.name: Leigh Paatsch
publication.name: Herald Sun (Australia)

quote: It's a fine and entertaining movie. Just lower your expectations before you sit down.
critic.name: Sean Collier
publication.name: Pittsburgh Magazine

quote: It's a master class on how to tell amazing stories. Must see. [Full Review in Spanish] - Cinergética
critic.name: David Ocadiz
publication.name: Cinergética

quote: Weird, sweet and worth a watch, but a symptom of an ongoing Hollywood problem.
critic.name: Hannah Strong
publication.name: Little White Lies

quote: I don't know what you're going to do after you see the movie, but this 46-year-old plans to return home, take his toys out of the closet and treat them to some long-overdue playtime.
critic.name: Cameron Meier
publication.name: Orlando Weekly

quote: Meta, existential Disney-Pixar cleverness about lost toys that find their purpose, bittersweet partings, happy reunions and how--as the old saying goes-one person's trash can, indeed, become someone else's treasure.
critic.name: Neil Pond
publication.name: Parade Magazine

quote: The series' saving grace is that, with humor and heart so beautifully wise and stunningly rendered (CGI pun intended), even as returns diminish, a new chapter is still warm and smartly entertaining.
critic.name: MaryAnn Johanson
publication.name: Flick Filosopher

quote: It's highly refreshing to see that the toys are ensconced in their rightful, traditional, existential capacity of enhancing children's imaginations. Nary a cellphone in sight.
critic.name: Mark Jackson
publication.name: Epoch Times

quote: As an ode to spunk, ingenuity, teamwork, storytelling and animation artistry, "Toy Story 4" fires on every spirited cylinder.
critic.name: Ann Hornaday
publication.name: Washington Post

quote: Big-hearted, touching finale to Pixar's legendary franchise.
critic.name: Sandie Angulo Chen
publication.name: Common Sense Media

quote: There was arguably no need to make a fourth Toy Story film, but this outing is undeniably funny and heartfelt and will give you all the warm and fuzzies that only Toy Story can.
critic.name: Sinead Brennan
publication.name: RTÉ (Ireland)

quote: Despite the immense talent, the traits and choices lack being truly worthwhile.
critic.name: Don Shanahan
publication.name: Every Movie Has a Lesson

quote: We're four levels deep into Toy Story now, so we know all the fun comes with deep personal reflection, and that's why these films resonate well into adulthood.
critic.name: Fred Topel
publication.name: Popdust

quote: It's an exciting, surprising, incredibly funny film that's just as poignant and heartfelt as you'd expect from this franchise.
critic.name: Germain Lussier
publication.name: io9.com

quote: An extremely enjoyable combination of earnest humanism and newly-sentient toys yearning for the sweet release of death.
critic.name: Vincent Mancini
publication.name: FilmDrunk

quote: You know you're not going to get out of a Pixar movie without tears, because we care about these characters and we care about the way they care about and for each other.
critic.name: Nell Minow
publication.name: Movie Mom

quote: Toy Story 4 is not as great as the original two, or as moving as the third installment, but it's a sweet summer movie that honors the innocent, creative spirit of childhood.
critic.name: Laura DeMarco
publication.name: Cleveland Plain Dealer

quote: Despite the film's quick pace and breezy good nature, the overall effect is mediocre, and Toy Story 4 is easily the weakest effort in the series so far.
critic.name: Kyle Smith
publication.name: National Review

quote: Did we really need another "Toy Story" movie? Turns out we did.
critic.name: Moira MacDonald
publication.name: Seattle Times

quote: "Toy Story 4" is genuinely gripping for most of the way, with just a couple of minor dips. But it arrives at a lovely place, with an embrace of life in all its danger and uncertainty.
critic.name: Mick LaSalle
publication.name: San Francisco Chronicle

quote: What transpires is a complex, wisened contemplation of a simple existence lived for a greater purpose - Pixar's most soulful film in years.
critic.name: Ella Kemp
publication.name: Culture Whisper

quote: Against the long-presumed insurmountable odds, 'Toy Story 4' proves the fourth time can still be the charm. How foolish we were to ever doubt Pixar.
critic.name: Doug Jamieson
publication.name: The Jam Report

quote: If you're looking for a reason to smile, Toy Story 4 will provide.
critic.name: Matthew Toomey
publication.name: ABC Radio (Australia)

quote: 'Toy Story 4' seems aimed at those of us who grew up with the franchise that first graced silver screens twenty-four years ago. However, it also re-opens the story for an entirely new generation.
critic.name: Utibe Gautt Ate
publication.name: Black Girl Nerds

quote: The big laughs are slow to arrive but they do make an appearance, and the joke spread spans all the ages, with lots of Easter eggs for the most dedicated fans.
critic.name: Alison Rowat
publication.name: The Herald (Scotland)

quote: Toy Story 4 is Pixar firing on all cylinders - it's a whole lot of fun and a whole lot of heart. It (potentially) wraps up the franchise in a nice bow and gives our old friends the final character arcs they so deserve.
critic.name: Brent Goldman
publication.name: culturevulture.net

quote: Pixar is notorious for reducing parents to puddles. Its movies are built from the pain of loss all explored here with tremendous sophistication.
critic.name: Larushka Ivan-Zadeh
publication.name: Metro Newspaper (UK)

quote: This franchise is so generous, and so obviously precious to those who work on it, that we shouldn't have doubted. This one more than justifies its existence. I'm ready for four more.
critic.name: Will Leitch
publication.name: Paste Magazine

quote: Forky alone is enough to elevate this potential cash-grab into the beautiful and hilarious coda that its long-running series needed to be truly complete.
critic.name: David Ehrlich
publication.name: indieWire

quote: More of a straightforward action comedy than the previous film, this is a delightful combination of engaging characters, spectacular animation and riotously hilarious storytelling.
critic.name: Rich Cline
publication.name: Shadows on the Wall

quote: Though Toy Story 4 is as funny and action-packed and as effective a tearjerker as is to be expected from this series, what's truly remarkable is Bo's evolution.
critic.name: Sherilyn Connelly
publication.name: SF Weekly

quote: Although one is sure that Toy Story 4 is not necessary... it turns out that Toy Story 4 is good. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Yago García
publication.name: Cinemanía (Spain)

quote: Depending on which eye is looking at you, Forky is either adorable or horrifying.
critic.name: Josh Larsen
publication.name: LarsenOnFilm

quote: It feels ridiculous that a film about the secret lives of toys could teach us so much about the dynamics of love, materialism, and psychological development, but here we have it.
critic.name: Joseph Walsh
publication.name: The Skinny

quote: Balancing action, comedy and misty-eyed emotion, this is yet another dazzling showcase of animation from the Pixar stable.
critic.name: James Mottram
publication.name: South China Morning Post

quote: You've still got a friend in them. Pixar has beaten the odds with "Toy Story 4," finding a moving and wholly unexpected way to continue Woody and company's adventures.
critic.name: Joey Magidson
publication.name: Hollywood News

quote: It will send you out of the theater laughing, crying, and thinking all at once, an appropriate mix of responses for what I hope, out of love, will be our last minutes with a franchise that's given us so much.
critic.name: Dana Stevens
publication.name: Slate

quote: If you see this as an epilogue to the series, it fits the description well, providing adequate footnotes to a story already so well-told...[this] is a film that we didn't think we needed, but I for one am happy with its existence.
critic.name: Ciaran Kerr
publication.name: Film Bunker

quote: The "Toy Story" saga felt fully complete without it, which makes this a movie that doesn't really need to exist, but whose existence doesn't diminish the whole, either.
critic.name: Bill Goodykoontz
publication.name: Arizona Republic

quote: This sequel may not be as buoyant as previous chapters, but the filmmakers' continued commitment to honoring these characters -- and to understanding what is so universal about their quest to love and be loved -- is worth treasuring.
critic.name: Tim Grierson
publication.name: Screen International

quote: Josh Cooley's direction keeps the pace sprightly and the voice cast and animators knock it out the park...
critic.name: Adam Fresco
publication.name: Flicks.co.nz

quote: Toy Story 4 is an utterly endearing joy, it had me cackling with laughter and sobbing with streams of tears.
critic.name: Ben Rolph
publication.name: Discussing Film

quote: Pixar once again proves they are able to create a film both kids and adults will enjoy. Toy Story 4 is heartfelt, comedic, and overall an entertaining and engaging experience!
critic.name: Jason Escamilla
publication.name: EskimoTV

quote: For his directorial debut, Josh Cooley did an amazing job of staying true to the legacy of the franchise while still adding new original ideas that felt authentic to the Toy Story lore.
critic.name: Dorian Parks
publication.name: Geeks of Color

quote: Hilarious start-to-finish with emotional twinges...it's just great.
critic.name: Mark Ellis
publication.name: Schmoes Know

quote: There was never a dull moment...consistently entertaining and yet again another fantastic Toy Story movie.
critic.name: Chris Stuckmann
publication.name: ChrisStuckmann.com

quote: Woody's search for purpose can be taken as a meta-textual commentary on the film itself - how to stretch a franchise that's already ended perfectly into another dollar or billion?
critic.name: Matt Oakes
publication.name: Silver Screen Riot

quote: "Toy Story 4's" sense of humor has also darkened by a few shades since the last go-round, leading to an overall, and very welcome, oddball sensibility. It's easily the funniest in the series.
critic.name: Witney Seibold
publication.name: Critically Acclaimed

quote: Toy Story 4 was the perfect way to wrap up one of the most successful and endearing franchises in history.
critic.name: Shannon McGrew
publication.name: Nightmarish Conjurings

quote: Toy Story 4 explodes with the very thing on which Pixar built its foundation: a goldmine of creativity.
critic.name: Louisa Moore
publication.name: Screen Zealots

quote: The animation is stellar, as is the direction from Cooley. It's all well-produced, but is more focused on providing a pleasant send-off to the characters that helped to define Pixar than it is to telling a story that needed to be told.
critic.name: Brandon Zachary
publication.name: CBR

quote: It bravely explores the essence of what it is that makes each of us matter beyond the functions we serve as workers or as members of a family.
critic.name: Oliver Jones
publication.name: Observer

quote: Forky may be the purest thing in Toy Story 4.
critic.name: Shana O'Neil
publication.name: Hypable

quote: We all grew up with Woody, Buzz, Bo Peep and their buddies. The new characters are just as fun. They all show true emotion so well, that will tug at your heart and even draw a tear.
critic.name: Linda and Al Lerner
publication.name: Movies and Shakers
