quote: Toy Story 4 proves the Disney and Pixar still can go back to their roots and create some of the most stunningly beautiful and emotionally touching films that will bring joy to all ages.
critic.name: Ashley Menzel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: A rousing journey brimming with warmth, humor and humanism. It's one of the best animated films of the year.
critic.name: Avi Offer
publication.name: NYC Movie Guru

quote: Toy Story 4 is perfectly fine. Even good! [But] at the ripe old age of 24, Toy Story is suddenly what it never used to be: disposable.
critic.name: Simon Miraudo
publication.name: Student Edge

quote: Toy Story 4 asks us to let it go.
critic.name: Michael Arbeiter
publication.name: Nerdist

quote: One thing that's kept the Toy Story franchise so solid after so many installments is its commitment to whatever emotional crisis its beloved gang of sentient toys is facing.
critic.name: Andrea Thompson
publication.name: A Reel of One's Own

quote: I don't think anything can surpass Toy Story 3 for emotional heft (If it didn't break you, you aren't human) so 4 wisely doesn't try. It makes up for it with laughs - lots of laughs.
critic.name: Jamie East
publication.name: The Sun (UK)

quote: Even if you don't emerge from Toy Story 4 feeling morally enriched, you'll surely have a spring in your step.
critic.name: Brian Viner
publication.name: Daily Mail (UK)

quote: Toy Story 4  is a film where you'll find your hearts feel warmer and your soul feels stronger. It is glorious.
critic.name: Jazz Tangcay
publication.name: Awards Daily

quote: If I had to get another Toy Story, this is about as strange and beguiling an entry as I could have hoped for.
critic.name: David Sims
publication.name: The Atlantic

quote: While the novelty will never be the same as it was the first time 24 years ago, curiosity and invention continue to be displayed in full force in the Toy Story movies. How's this for praise: I left smiling. And that really counts, sometimes.
critic.name: Blake Goble
publication.name: Consequence

quote: It takes some kind of genius for the Pixar animators to give such a searing emotional charge to a story in which one of the main characters is a single use plastic spork retrieved from the trash.
critic.name: Geoffrey Macnab
publication.name: Independent (UK)

quote: The best comedy of the summer is a Pixar sequel.
critic.name: Jonathan W. Hickman
publication.name: Daily Film Fix

quote: Although it sticks to the rescue plot of previous films, Toy Story 4 is much richer for how it challenges its characters and conventions with a powerful dose of humor and heart.
critic.name: Matt Goldberg
publication.name: Collider

quote: The new movie goes smaller, acting more as a coda to the original three films instead of a larger extension of them.
critic.name: Don Kaye
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: We're all Forkys at heart, the film seems to be saying. And by breaking out of the cozy boundaries of the Toy Story films, it lights out for new, uncertain territory.
critic.name: Bilge Ebiri
publication.name: New York Magazine/Vulture

quote: I thought it was delightful
critic.name: Rachel Wagner
publication.name: Rachel's Reviews (YouTube)

quote: Justifies its own existence following up a perfect ending with yet another emotional stranglehold of closure
critic.name: Robert Kojder
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: We may have boxed up the old toys but for them and for us, the story is never really over. It just changes.
critic.name: Travis Hopson
publication.name: Punch Drunk Critics

quote: I still think that Toy Story ended perfectly as a trilogy, but if you can give me a fourth installment that lives up to the legacy, then I am totally game... The adventure is great, it's fun, it's funny, and it's relevant.
critic.name: Jeremy Jahns
publication.name: JeremyJahns.com

quote: Cute, but anti-climactic
critic.name: Roger Moore
publication.name: Movie Nation

quote: Toy Story 4 delivers a cinematic grand slam, a nine-years-later sequel that's wholly equal to the high expectations raised by the terrific trio that it follows.
critic.name: Brian Lowry
publication.name: CNN.com

quote: The actors are certainly game to be as strong as ever in their vocal performances, which has Toy Story 4 working effectively as an animated character study, but the film is also flat-out hysterical.
critic.name: Aaron Neuwirth
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: Some of the new characters here are excellent! But once again, Pixar delivers more message than story. Also you will cry. Not a bad movie at all, but not a GREAT movie either.
critic.name: Grace Randolph
publication.name: Beyond the Trailer

quote: An existential rumination on feeling unwanted and finding new purpose in life, while also being a blast.
critic.name: Kyle Pinion
publication.name: The Beat

quote: Toy Story 4 might have sounded like an unnecessary addition to the franchise nine years after the perfect ending to a beloved trilogy, but it fits in wonderfully and expands on what's gone before.
critic.name: Rosie Fletcher
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: A more than worthy finale to the series that's as funny, entertaining and emotional as the first three movies.
critic.name: Edward Douglas
publication.name: The Weekend Warrior

quote: Toy Story 4 is exceptional on so many levels. Non-stop laughs, jaw-dropping animation, and an especially touching chapter of Woody's journey. If you want to walk out of a movie feeling hopeful about the endless possibilities out there, this one's a must.
critic.name: Perri Nemiroff
publication.name: Collider Video

quote: Stands shoulder-to-shoulder with the other films in the Toy Story franchise. It's a great movie.
critic.name: Dan Murrell
publication.name: Screen Junkies

quote: Disney and Pixar continue to deliver greatness. Toy Story 4 combines hysterical humor with an abstract, emotionally complex plot. The film is a banner sequel on all fronts.
critic.name: Julian Roman
publication.name: MovieWeb

quote: exciting charm-bomb of animated adventure, which is a delightful and irresistible addition
critic.name: Chris Hunneysett
publication.name: Daily Mirror (UK)

quote: Rest assured, if nothing else, Toy Story 4 fulfills its series' mandate to leave you a blubbering mess by the ending credits.
critic.name: Clint Worthington
publication.name: The Spool

quote: As Bo leads us through the adventure, she ditches the skirt. Staff in hand, with a glint in her eye, she evokes Charlton Heston and Harrison Ford, with touches of Bogart as well as Bacall.
critic.name: Rubin Safaya
publication.name: Cinemalogue

quote: Pixar's Toy Story 4 has heart and humor to spare in one more adventure with Woody and the gang, exploring tough themes through toys new and old.
critic.name: Molly Freeman
publication.name: Screen Rant

quote: Sweet Lord, this is good.
critic.name: Kevin Maher
publication.name: Times (UK)

quote: Cooley's well-told, exquisitely beautiful finale is perhaps only "very good" in comparison to the Toy stories that came before it, but a victory lap feels like more than enough...
critic.name: Todd Gilchrist
publication.name: Birth.Movies.Death.

quote: Quite simply, if you're a Toy Story fan and are planning to avoid Toy Story 4 because the trilogy ended so perfectly, you'll be missing out.
critic.name: Ian Sandwell
publication.name: Digital Spy

quote: Toy Story 5 now seems like a rather good idea.
critic.name: Jamie Graham
publication.name: Total Film

quote: Let this be a lesson to all franchise cynics: Sometimes more is actually good.
critic.name: Lindsey Bahr
publication.name: Associated Press

quote: Toy Story 4 could very well be a satisfying conclusion and the end of the line for the 24-year-old Disney-Pixar franchise.
critic.name: Danielle Solzman
publication.name: Solzy at the Movies

quote: As is true of the best Pixar movies, a carefully teased-out deeper meaning acts in rich concert with the fun and eye-popping stuff.
critic.name: Richard Lawson
publication.name: Vanity Fair

quote: It's a smaller, less moving, and mercifully, less traumatising entertainment than the last one, less satisfying in its plotting and less provocative in its themes.
critic.name: Nicholas Barber
publication.name: BBC.com

quote: Toy Story 4's purpose, in the end, is to help you find yours.
critic.name: Angie Han
publication.name: Mashable

quote: Bring some Kleenex and get ready to cry your heart out.
critic.name: Kate Gardner
publication.name: The Mary Sue

quote: It might not take us to the epic highs of its predecessors - which is, to be fair, a skyscraping bar to reach - but Toy Story 4 is certainly the strongest fourth series instalment since Mad Max hit that Fury Road.
critic.name: Dan Jolin
publication.name: Empire Magazine

quote: This is a funny, clever, inventive, richly endearing film.
critic.name: Nigel Andrews
publication.name: Financial Times

quote: A minor epilogue to a major work that's mostly good enough to stand as its own entity and almost good enough to peek all the way out from under its predecessor's shadow.
critic.name: Bob Chipman
publication.name: Escapist Magazine

quote: Another fun adventure from Pixar, even if it doesn't quite reach the heights of its predecessors. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mikel Zorrilla
publication.name: Espinof

quote: The prime mover, and the heart of "Toy Story 4," remains Woody, whose eternal mission to save lost toys takes on a new dimension and provides a fitting conclusion to this beloved character.
critic.name: Sean P. Means
publication.name: Salt Lake Tribune

quote: Toy Story 4 is the surprisingly much-needed epilogue, featuring everything you could hope for in a Pixar film, and is sure to be the family event of the summer.
critic.name: Griffin Schiller
publication.name: The Playlist

quote: With this third sequel to Toy Story, Pixar has gotten away with pushing its own expiration date on the series. But those tiny spork tines won't hold it together much longer. It's time to get lost.
critic.name: Scott Tobias
publication.name: The Verge

quote: TOY STORY 4 is another home run for Pixar and one that perfectly sets up future movies (or Disney+ series) with characters new and old. It also works wonderfully as a conclusion to the series.
critic.name: Alex Maidy
publication.name: JoBlo's Movie Network

quote: For the fourth outing from a group of cartoon characters who've been at it since 1995, it's a pretty decent ride.
critic.name: Kelsea Stahler
publication.name: Refinery29

quote: In Woody's search for love, Toy Story 4 reminds us how hard it is to let go.
critic.name: Alex Abad-Santos
publication.name: Vox

quote: "Toy Story 4" ends on a respectable, bittersweet note that would make the perfect bookend to this likable franchise. But so did the last movie.
critic.name: Johnny Oleksinski
publication.name: New York Post

quote: If this movie doesn't touch your heart, you'd have to be as lifeless as the toys pretend to be when humans are in the vicinity.
critic.name: Richard Roeper
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times

quote: A terrific adventure comedy and an appropriate franchise extension that works as a parable for Pixar's own evolution.
critic.name: Scott Mendelson
publication.name: Forbes

quote: Pixar could easily retire this series with a clean sweep of films that have been lovely to look at and moving and funny to watch. But if they can maintain this level of wonderful, keep 'em coming.
critic.name: Alonso Duralde
publication.name: TheWrap

quote: Toy Story 4 does an even better job than Toy Story 3 of managing mature themes while remaining kid-friendly.
critic.name: Karen Han
publication.name: Polygon

quote: The film seamlessly interweaves fun escapades and earnest emotions, but it lacks the visual power of its predecessor.
critic.name: Pat Brown
publication.name: Slant Magazine

quote: While Toy Story 3 felt like the perfect ending for these characters, Toy Story 4 offers an unexpected epilogue that's just as meaningful as the films that came before it. It may not have been necessary, but somehow, it still feels right.
critic.name: Laura Prudom
publication.name: IGN Movies

quote: Despite the endless speculations on whether they could pull off yet another sequel, it's safe to say that Pixar didn't flinch, and the result is as satisfying as anyone would've hoped.
critic.name: Linda Marric
publication.name: The Jewish Chronicle

quote: It took Pixar decades of technological innovation, but they finally made a beautiful piece of trash.
critic.name: Darren Franich
publication.name: Entertainment Weekly

quote: Individual odysseys are engaging and voicework is downright heavenly.
critic.name: Brian Orndorf
publication.name: Blu-ray.com
